  "text": "Ago2 has also been shown to enhance miRNA-mediated knockdown with perfectly matched binding sites [CITATION_1] . Because of perfect complementarity between the miR-361-3p and 3′ UTR of DUSP2 mRNA, the wild-type DUSP2 Luciferase construct was used to verify Ago2enhanced knockdown. As expected, the reporter activity was suppressed by miR-361-3p, and tremendously suppressed by co-expression with Ago2 ( Fig. 6f ). Therefore, we considered that Ago2 might promote miR-361-3pinduced DUSP2 mRNA decay by enhancing its knockdown efficacy.",
